9 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to require that an
10 employer continue a legislator’s employment benefits during a legislative leave
11 at the same level and rate of contribution as when the legislator is not on leave.
12 An act relating to fair employment practices and legislative leave
13 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
14 Sec. 1. 21 V.S.A. § 496 is amended to read:
15 § 496. LEGISLATIVE LEAVE
16 (a) Any employee who, in order to serve as a member of the General
17 Assembly, must leave a full-time position in the employ of any employer, shall
18 be entitled to a temporary or partial leave of absence for the purpose of
19 allowing the employee to perform any official duty in connection with the
20 employee’s elected office. The leave of absence shall not cause loss of job
