1 status, seniority, or the right to participate in insurance and other employee
2 benefits during the leave of absence. The employer shall continue employment
3 benefits for the duration of the leave at the level and under the conditions
4 coverage would be provided if the employee continued in employment
5 continuously for the duration of the legislative leave. The employer may
6 require that the employee contribute to the cost of the benefits during the leave
7 at the existing rate of employee contribution. The employee shall continue to
8 accrue seniority for the duration of the leave at the same level as if the
9 employee were employed continuously for the duration of the legislative leave.
10 Further, an employer shall not discharge or in any other matter retaliate against
11 an employee who exercises or attempts to exercise the employee’s rights to
12 serve as an elected official.
13 * * *
14 Sec. 2. EFFECTIVE DATE
15 This act shall take effect on July 1, 2025.
